The paper focuses on analyzing work routines in online knowledge collaboration, which falls under the scope of computer-supported cooperative work (CSCW). Therefore, cs.CSCW is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a data set and methods from fields like bio-informatics, which suggests a potential overlap with sub-categories like cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.IR (information retrieval). Additionally, the paper analyzes revisions to Wikipedia articles, which could fall under sub-categories like cs.DL (digital libraries) and cs.SOC (social and economic networks).
